content.detailedDescription:
I was visiting a friend in germany when we were sitting outside on a clear warm night.Long story short the subject of satelites came up and i always see one on a clear night if you look long enough.
we both spoted one and observed it for about 20sec going in a steady direction just like satelites do,when it sudden changed a 90 degree direction and disapeared 3 seconds later.
the distance,size and speed were exactly the one of a satelite.
i'm pretty sure a satelite (or anything else ) is not able to do that.
we're not sure what we saw or make sense of what object could do such a sudden maneuvor and if it was in space with high speed like a satelite would travel.
i never wrote to mufon or anybody else and wouldn't if i was the only witness but let me know if this is something else or could be explained.
probably nothing exciting but thought i put it out there for some thoughts.
thx - roland
content.summary: Star/satelite watching with friend

content.detailedDescription: I love looking at the stars on clear nights and tonight was cloudless at the time. i was looking at the stars and i saw this object. it was flying low, maybe around 500ft or so, almost directly over my house. it was triangular in shape and had three lights near each angle. it was traveling at approximately 100-200 mph and i was only observing it for approximately five seconds before it faded away in what appeared to be it cloaking itself. when it was visible it seemed like it was already semi cloaked and the three lights were not bright but still visible enough to where i could make out it's triangular shape and exact placement of it's lights. this object made zero noise. i was a military police officer and have seen some questionable things in the sky but never anything like this. absolutely amazing experience! i live in a heavily populated area with a heavy military presence. there are always aircraft in the sky. after i observed this object i continued to look at the sky and observed aircraft flying in ways they normally don't as if the were searching for something.
content.summary: This object was flying very low, made no noise

content.detailedDescription: I was driving north to work on hwy 32 about 2-3 miles south of holt and observed something with a blinking green light on back and solid red light on front (the lights were about the size of a pea at arms length) and was traveling at about the same speed as an aircraft in a north direction. i paid it no mind at that point, thinking it was just an airplane, but about 2 minutes later i notice a green light (which looked a bit elongated almost like 2 pea size lights right next to each other) traveling in a northeast direction. i had to lean forward in my drivers seat to observe it fully. it traveled for only a couple seconds in this direction then dove down in what seemed like a northward direction. i thought i was witnessing a plane crash because it abruptly shot down, but then the lights just completely dissapeared even though the thing was still well above the tree line. later when i got to work i heard other people had seen strange lights in the sky also, at about the same time as me, but i'm not sure if they saw the same thing or not.I did notice the radio acting funny before seeing the first light, as well.
content.summary: Saw elongated green light traveling across the sky which suddenly changed directions and broke in two before blinking out completely.

content.detailedDescription:
Filled out at mufon headquarters, with witness on the phone, by l. flechtner 18809, on january 18th, 2017
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

my wife and i were going to dinner at the indian casino during the week and 
while traveling north on hwy 80 near 5th street my wife saw what she at first thought were fireworks.
when we looked closer they appeared to be several sparkling electrical bursts. within the burst we could see a silver shimmer and a hugh black craft materialized. it had volkswagen size lights on the side of it. one was green and one was blue. three pickup sized bursts of red translucent light/flames shot out of it, one at a time. dark pillow like clouds seemed to be surrounding it, the clouds were low to the ground and seemed to surround the black, disc shaped, two story high craft.
the craft made no noise and was about two hundred feet off the ground. we were about a mile from it. the area has no homes where it was hovering, just a wilderness area.
we were traveling about 55 mph and traveling towards it. we slowed down when we saw it to get a better view, but had to speed up when a car came up behind us. we turned towards a clear cut area to get a better look, the the clouds and the craft were gone. we saw just darkness. the whole thing lasted about 45 seconds.

we saw a white vehicle that said homeland security on it go by, kind of strange. when we got to the casino for dinner several other people said they had seen two other homeland security vehicles in the area as well.

there is a military air base close by and the next day jets were doing scrambling maneuvers all over the area.

fort mccoy and fort douglas are near by.
content.summary: While traveling on hwy 80 near 5th street my wife and i saw electrical sparks and saw a huge black craft appear

content.detailedDescription: We were on our balcony on the 11th floor when we seen this blinking object moving we were having a smoke and watching the traffic. we did not think of it too much until we came back out. we the recorded the object for a few minutes on our balcony just hovering over near another building. we do not believe it was a drone the size of this object i bet could fit 30 people on it. this was a big object and we have it on video, we recently just discovered this website from facebook and a person named steve hudgeons jr asked me to email him the vide so we did then he told us to fill out this report. we are hoping to find answers about what we saw. we lost sight of object because at that time my fiancee cat was dying and we needed to take care of her so we could not stay recording the object. about an hour or so after it was gone when i went back to balcony to chek with vide recorder again. i will upload the video to the media attachments and i will also send a picture of what it looks like in the day time showing its country land with no towers or lights in that part of the video.
content.summary: Looked large blinking lights (video recorded)

content.detailedDescription:
I'm a tow boat pilot steering/ navigating  barges/tow up river, and saw this big bright light going back, forth, up, down,and side to side. i thought it was a helicopter searching for something, but couldn't see the red, green, or flashing light on it. when i got closer i turned on my search lights to  navigate  an area of the river, and the object stopped moving. then flew away in a straight line about 20 miles, and made a u turn back towards my direction. then started over the tree line, then over the river, and evently above my vessel. it flowed me for about 10 minutes up river, above my boat. it had two huge light at each end of the craft, and this strange symbol ? or patterned on the belly of the craft, in between the two huge lights.
at first i kept trying to read it, to see what it says, but gave up. cause it wasn't writing ? it's was some kind of symbol, or pattern. i ran into my pilot house it get my iphone to record it, and when i was in my pilot house i noticed it out of my forward port window it turned, and was turning away, leaving. i so grabbed my iphone looked where it went, and it was on the western bank, the morgantown side above the tree line. it was  just a ball of light again like i seen in the  beginning . i snapped a picture of it, and it started picking up speed, and shot away at high speed around a bulinding, high rise building.
saw it again 3 days later at the drive inn with my girl freind, but it was 20/30 miles away.
just a ball of light, like a comet with no trail, or tail.
1 year later found a mysterious crop circle, and in the formation every plant  node  was  swallen, and bend it in the same way, a 45 degree angle just in the formation ( thousands of plants like this to make formation ), not outside the crop formation.  took plant samples also, and many pictures/videos.
the craft when i first saw it was  probably  500ft of the ground. when it hovered above my boat, and i was outside the pilot house looking up at it. it was probably less than 500ft, cause my pilot house is raised 38 ft in the air. i could see this thing clearly!!!!
i have a picture of it before it shot away. i was looking up,at this thing for at least 10 minutes. it was like it was checking me out. the way the thing went far out of its way, then back towards my direction, then evently above my boat, well u can tell it was strategic.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: It's was very bright, like one huge led cigartylenol shaped 2 huge lights/pattern belly of cra

content.detailedDescription:
A group of seagulls appeared to be flying above a chemtrail outside of my home on wednesday, january 18, 2016, but when i looked closer i noticed something odd. they were not seagulls. they were morphing orbs that took the form of seagulls. the continued to morphed and glow right before my eyes until they vanished into thin air. it was bizarre. 

this was not an illusion caused by reflecting sunlight. there were other birds nearby that didn't glow, morph, shape-shift, swirl into the sky, and vanish. this was a group of white ufo orbs playing in a chemtrail.  the appeared in the chemtrail and vanished near the chemtrail.  they did not fly into that spot and fly away.  the appeared and disappeared right near the center of the chemtrail.
content.summary: Glowing white orbs

content.detailedDescription: I was driving on i-5 south from marysville into everett and i saw a very large glowing orb in the sky, the biggest i have seen (likely due to it being the closest i have seen). my perception of the size from where i was made it seem to be about 30ft diameter while it was glowing the most. it was about 5:35 that i noticed it and i was about a mile past exit 199. the color was orange/ copper. at fist it was stationary in the sky, then the glow got bigger and it moved west. from where i was on the freeway it seemed like the craft was almost directly above the everett navy base (about 1 mile from me). once it got to that position it looked like it stopped moving and slowly started to fade until it got very faint, stayed that way briefly and then it was gone.
content.summary: Big glowing craft went towards everett navy base

content.detailedDescription:
I went to my window at home (building at 8th floor) when i saw high intensity light between white and light blue. the intensity changed during observation, sometimes with very strong radiation and some kind of aura around the object. observed some seconds and get cellphone to take some pics. 

the object remained stationary with very slow descending path. i felt very surprised because never saw any object with that size and light intensity. my mother and brother was with me and observed the same. 

i have lost contact after 30 minutes because of descending path. the object came down between other buildings.
content.summary: Stationary object with high intensity light between white and light blue. much bigger than any star and venus.
content.locationName: Rio de Janeiro, State of Rio de Janeiro

content.detailedDescription:
I was on a ride with friends near playa panama on culebra bay in the province of guanacaste, costa rica, we stopped to take pictures of the bay at about 14:00 we took several pictures and got on our bikes and rode home it was not until today 01/18/2017 that i uploaded and viewed them on my computer. after looking i found one picture that had an object in the right corner so i zoomed in on it, it does not look like a plane or a bird to me it has a distinct disk shape when zoomed in. i did not see it when the picture was taken or afterward only when i reviewed my pictures.
the camera that i used is a sony cybershot set to auto so if it was a bird the auto focus would have picked it as being the closer object i think.
content.summary: Reviewed pictures from a ride and noticed an object in the right corner of a picture

content.detailedDescription: It was my girlfriends birthday, so on our way home, we crossed a bridge and i noticed 2 bright orange lights, low and i told her to stop, so we pulled over on the bridge. i thought they were typhoon aircraft with their afterburners on. she witnessed it too. as i opened my window, i noticed that they weren't moving and no noise. i told her to put her foot down and follow them. we ended up pulling over down welland road and would you believe, in front of a police officer who was talking to some young lad. we both got out the car and one of the orange lights had gone and i had noticed the altitude climb as it appeared smaller, though still bright. it hovered there for a good few minutes. police officer also starred at it. a few minutes later, it headed west and its acceleration was incredible. my hair stood on end. we then went home in silence. i called my step dad as he is a member of the fighter control website to see if there has been any aircraft flying over this area we was at. it was a negative, nothing was flying. the day after, 2 pilots reported in the paper that two orange lights or ufo's had been spotted over the isle of wight. i believed these to possibly have been what we had seen.
content.summary: first noticed low over city moving. we followed them until one was directly above us.

content.detailedDescription: Came out of the house to cool down looked up and said i used to see satellites as a child regularly and haven't seen one in years then a very faint star moving at satellite speed looked like a star assumed iss came from the north very high altitude almost a straight line as it came over brisbane moving towards our suburb in the south moved down the coast expected iss or satellite trajectory as it got past 90' it arced out towards the east and disappeared at 120' se from original sighting heading south east ten seconds later its completed a turn and heading max speed back up the coast heading north. have seen many aircraft no noise to high to be a plane and moving fast very fast disappeared heading north again. iss over indonesia check flight radar no reported aircraft flying the circuit to brisbane airport in that manner.
content.summary: Fast moving star changed direction

content.detailedDescription: My sister and i were siting outside looking at the stars and smoking a cigarette. we noticed a star that looked like it was moving back and forth slightly, then we looked around a little more and saw what we at first thought was a satellite, we started comparing the two, and our attention was locked on the new object. the object was moving towards our direction at a quick rate, looking as if it was above the stars. the object had flashing lights, in a pattern i didn't recognize from everyday aircrafts. the object seemed like it was almost a few blocks away from us, descending, when it switched directions in the sky, heading towards lake superior. seconds later it switched directions again, going over us at an angle, and then again a few more seconds after that. we then watched the object until it vanished before our eyes. the lights, red, were flickering in an unusual pattern, while a white light remained visible almost the entire time.
content.summary: My sister and i were outside looking at stars and we noticed an object moving towards us

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting at home, a friend had called me to confirm he wasnt going crazy with what he was seeing, hes a few miles away from me and he said look south southeast, being miles apart and finding object in same direction indicated to me it was far away from earth, but within orbit because it wasnt a star, at this point i grabbed my binoculars and searched the sky, only took a minute to find it because the location of the ufo, had a black background (no stars) and (no clouds) obscuring my vision...I couldnt see an actual solid object to whatever the lights were attatched to, but it had one central super bright white light and was constant but all around the wgite light were randomly blinking lights 3 or 4 at a time with shades of red green blue and possibly yellow,at times the colored lights would stay on briefly, i believe object is square because the lights were on each side of the bright white one, so like one in the top left corner, top right corner, etc., the object still! hasnt moved and does not remind me of any type of aircraft, blimp, helicopter, or any type of satellite, it was about 9pm then, and its 9:54 pm now still there, still no movement whatsoever, i dont know if its anything at all! but it grabbed my attention enough to fill out this report so i felt it important to pass it on.
content.summary: Friend called to look in sky, looked with binoculars, object had a central white light whole time, blinking lights of multiple colors lights of multiple colors rany not typical of a satelite, didnt move but seemed to morph structure of central light

content.detailedDescription: In april of 1993, i and a friend were at lum park in brainerd mn. this park is on a lake and it was about 8:00pm at night and we parked the car near a picnic area with a covered roof. we were about 20-25 feet from were we parked the car and i noticed some lights shine on the car from above. "yellowish" at first. there were no other cars around and i said something to my friend about the light. as we were looking around, another light, "blueish" started to spin on top of the car, and it was brighter. that's weird? i thought, there was not any car lights or flashlight that i knew of that could do that. the only way to describe it was it looked like it was right out of the movie, close encounters of the 3rd kind. where the truck was lite up by that ufo at the railroad tracks...You know those kind of lights. we looked on for about a minute and didn't hear any noise and there wasn't anyone around that we could see, no one playing tricks on us with lights nearby. so, at the same time we both stepped out and looked up in the sky...There were lots of pine trees around and we couldn't see anything where it could have been coming from, it was dark. even more odd was...At that moment when we had just looked up to see where the lights were coming from...The beeper i had in my purse started squealing beeps i had never heard before. i reached in my purse to grab it and turn it off...It startled me so much at just that moment. i tried to turn it off, but it wouldn't stop. so, i had to open it and take out the batteries. (it was maybe 20 seconds) and when i looked up again and then at the car...The lights were gone!
content.summary: No visual on craft, just lights

content.detailedDescription: Was inside my home watching tv.  out of the blue, i asked for the star beings to come out so i could see them again.  i went out to my front sidewalk and looked up in the sky to look for them.  my wife came out about 3 minutes later and was also looking.  i said "there they are".  it was brighter than a star.  referring to a clock position, it stopped at approx. the 3:00 position.  then it moved downward in a sw "arc" direction to the 6:00 position and grew larger and brighter for approx. 3-5 seconds.  it then dimmed and moved upward to the 9:00 position and then slowly disappeared.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Observed glowing object in sky that stopped, brightened, dimmed and changed direction.

content.detailedDescription:
I am guessing it was 1954, i was a 6 year old playing in my back yard in an industrial area in central scotland. about half a mile from my location there was a large iron works with tall chimney stacks.
i observed what i interpreted as a bicycle tyre being thrown up in air. it flew over the tops of the chimney stacks and past over head disappearing over the rooftops in the distance.
although i was a mere six year old i was puzzled as to how someone could throw a tyre to that height and for such a long distance.
at 67 i have only ever told this story one or twice but have often wondered what i witnessed. the direction was from north west to south east.
content.summary: It looked like a bicycle tyre that had been in the air

content.detailedDescription: I was with my 12 year old daughter leaving her junior high school near our home on a clear spring day 2005. it was around 3-4:00. we were in route to go pick up my two sons at the high school few blocks away. i was driving west on w. boyer st. when i looked up to my right by the railroad tracks, from the front windshield and we both see this huge swirling upside down tornado it swirling these papers that were in the colors of silver, copper, gold and other metallic colors. with the sun you can really see that the papers were shiny and metallic, all these papers had symbols printed on them. the symbols on the papers we could not identify but know they were symbols and not words.They were falling all around but would then disappear. i stopped at the stop sign. and made a quick left onto hoefgen ave. i though i could get off right there and looked to see if i could find one of the papers and get some but couldn't find one at all. there are two businesses there a small car sales and a lot with 18 wheeler beds. these papers flew all above there on top of the lots and disappeared. i think maybe two other people stopped to see this too. this phenomenon was very high and fast swirling and just like that stopped and disappeared. my daughter and i couldn't believe it and have told several people since and they don't understand what we saw and to this day we still remember it exactly the same and pass by there everyday, because it is two blocks by our home. we do not know what it was and what the meaning of this was in any way. sometimes i feel it was a type of portal. also, i have to add that we looked above and saw no helicopter, no airplane or anything like that in the sky above this. this is something we will never forget and finally i am able after all these years to report this to someone. i must add that if i had a cell phone then that could take video or photos i would have. but i only had a phone to make calls at that time. i regret not having any type of camera with me.
content.summary: Swirling upside down tornado with papers falling and disappearing.

content.summary: I look up and saw  these cigar and egg shaped craft with beams of light and they were pointed at the ground in my area
